definitions.definition: Utmost measure or extent ; highest state or degree ; the state, position, or moment of fullness ; fill .
examples: I was fed to the full .

definitions.definition: The phase of the moon when its entire face is illuminated, full moon .
A flip involving a complete turn in midair.
An aerialist maneuver consisting of a backflip in conjunction and simultaneous with a complete twist .

main_definition: Utmost measure or extent ; highest state or degree ; the state, position, or moment of fullness ; fill .
